I had issues building with Java 21, and it was because Paketo does not include buildpacks for Java 21 (see https://paketo.io/docs/howto/java/#jvm-default-version). So I had to specify the following buildpacks for the plugin:

 - `gcr.io/paketo-buildpacks/bellsoft-liberica:10.4.2` (according to https://github.com/paketo-buildpacks/bellsoft-liberica/releases)
 - `gcr.io/paketo-buildpacks/java-native-image`

As you already have, `BP_JVM_VERSION` must be `21.0.0`, and `BP_NATIVE_IMAGE` must be `true`.

So the maven configuration should look like:

```
 &lt;build&gt;
        &lt;plugins&gt;
            &lt;plugin&gt;
                &lt;groupId&gt;org.graalvm.buildtools&lt;/groupId&gt;
                &lt;artifactId&gt;native-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;/plugin&gt;
            &lt;plugin&gt;
                &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
                &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                &lt;configuration&gt;
                    &lt;image&gt;
                        &lt;buildpacks&gt;
                            &lt;buildpack&gt;gcr.io/paketo-buildpacks/java-native-image&lt;/buildpack&gt;
                            &lt;buildpack&gt;gcr.io/paketo-buildpacks/bellsoft-liberica:10.4.2&lt;/buildpack&gt;
                        &lt;/buildpacks&gt;
                        &lt;env&gt;
                            &lt;BP_JVM_VERSION&gt;21.0.0&lt;/BP_JVM_VERSION&gt;
                            &lt;BP_NATIVE_IMAGE&gt;true&lt;/BP_NATIVE_IMAGE&gt;
                        &lt;/env&gt;
                    &lt;/image&gt;
                &lt;/configuration&gt;
            &lt;/plugin&gt;
        &lt;/plugins&gt;
    &lt;/build&gt;
```


This is the task configuration for Gradle in case it helps someone:

```
tasks.named(&#39;bootBuildImage&#39;) {
    
